data.name: Herb-Infused Honey Glazed Pork Tenderloin
data.quickTastyDescription: A succulent pork tenderloin glazed with a sweet and aromatic herb-infused honey, perfect for a delightful dinner with minimal effort!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, combine honey, olive oil, rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, salt, and pepper to create the glaze.
Place the pork tenderloin on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Brush the herb-infused honey glaze generously over the pork tenderloin.
Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 145째F (63째C).
Remove from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve warm with your favorite sides.
